================================================================================
  OBJECT: Process__c
  DESCRIPTION: Master record for BPMN process diagrams
  
  AUTHOR: Dennis van Musschenbroek (DvM) - Cobra CRM B.V.
  CREATED: 2024-12-12
  VERSION: 1.0.0
  API VERSION: 62.0
  
  EXPLANATION:
  ============
  This is the central object in the Process Modeling Studio. Each Process__c
  record represents one complete BPMN diagram containing:
  
  1. Canvas_JSON__c - The complete diagram state (shapes, positions, connections)
     This is the SOURCE OF TRUTH for the visual diagram editor.
  
  2. Related BPMN_Element__c records - Individual shapes stored as child records
     for reporting, searching, and linking to other Salesforce data.
  
  3. Related BPMN_Connection__c records - Sequence flows between elements
     for understanding process flow and analyzing paths.
  
  4. Version history via Process_Version__c - Snapshots of published versions
     for audit trail and rollback capability.
  
  5. Assessment scores via Process_Assessment__c - Maturity, complexity,
     strategic importance, and risk ratings.
  
  DATA ARCHITECTURE:
  ==================
  The dual storage approach (JSON + related records) provides:
  - Fast canvas loading/saving via JSON
  - Native Salesforce reporting via related records
  - Search capability across all process elements
  - Linking process steps to Cases, Opportunities, etc.
  
  RELATIONSHIPS:
  ==============
  - Category__c (Lookup to Process_Category__c)
  - Process_Owner__c (Lookup to User)
  - BPMN_Elements (Master-Detail child)
  - BPMN_Connections (Master-Detail child)
  - Versions (Master-Detail child)
  - Assessments (Master-Detail child)
  
-->
